commit.message:
Extend use_zero_crc check to AF_CONN sockets (#690)

The `use_zero_crc` flag is already considered for AF_INET address family.
This commit ensures that when transmitting using sockets created with the
AF_CONN address family, crc32c calculation is skipped based on this flag.

commit.message: Further improve shutting down the read side of a socket
Improve shutting down of the read side of a socket
Improve handling of socket which was shutdown for reading
Improve handling of SHUTDOWN and SHUTDOWN ACK chunks
Cleanup graceful shutdown of the peer
Remove check already done by caller
Do not clear sb_cc when the write side is shutdown
